title: The Beatles Today - South Korea unofficial compilation (LP Rip)
description:
A compilation of the post-breakup solo recordings by George Harrison, John Lennon, Paul McCartney and Ringo Starr, that was released in South Korea on LP sometime in mid-1970-s as the 'new album' by The Beatles. Sound quality isn't pretty, but that's what you would expect from this kind of release. This LP was labeled as 'Vol. 2', that means that there is at least one more 'unknown' 'album' by The Beatles! ;)


01 George Harrison - What Is Life
02 George Harrison - If Not For You
03 George Harrison - My Sweet Lord
04 The Beatles - Something
05 The Beatles - Birthday
06 The Beatles - Yellow Submarine
07 John Lennon - Oh My Love
08 John Lennon - Love
09 Paul McCartney - Band On The Run
10 Paul McCartney - Junior's Farm
11 George Harrison - Ding Dong, Ding Dong
12 George Harrison - Dark Horse
13 Ringo Starr - No-No Song
14 Ringo Starr - Only You
15 John Lennon - Stay By Me


Happy birthday, John!
